choices.text:
memorising the Chinese dictionary. As a Burma student

in Singapore, I had trouble understanding the professors.

As an inn owner in Japan, I wonder about the lost cash

from the Japanese burglars and how to balance accounts.

As a retired woman in Italy, I wonder about my friends

and the flowers. But as I read the big news headlines,

as I watch the dramas unfolding in your local headlines,

as I gaze at you, still standing, as you run for one hour,

enjoying the cold, winter breeze,

I wonder why you’re still standing.

Jayasiri Sadasiva Rupasinghe, who was born in Burma, is a author, translator and doyen of rights has been the chief editor at Times Press. He lived in Singapore and studied at the Nanyang Technological University. His last book, released in 2017, is “Janaparahalli Ramakrishna Adyaksharu: Shabdavishwakavana“
